<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1405,2009]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1441,1467]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[447,542,1442,1468]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[447,542,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,652,1442,1468]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[548,652,1442,1468]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have (1) claw sheath, present, (2) contact between the nasal and rostral scales, absent, (3) scales in contact with the nasal scale, four, (4) postnasal scales, one, (5) position of the nostril in the nasal scale, central, (6) keels on dorsal body scales, absent, (7) digits per limb, five, (8) longest toe lamellae, 16–17, (9) dorsal scale rows, 96, (10) relative head width, 12.0, (11) relative rostral height, 50.1, (12) relative frontonasal length, 2.46, (13) relative interparietal distance, 0.632, (14) relative axilla-groin distance, 60.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1405,2009]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
From 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[267,377,1622,1648]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[267,377,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[385,491,1622,1648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[385,491,1622,1648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[675,770,1622,1648]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[675,770,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[778,883,1622,1648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[778,883,1622,1648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,261,1658,1684]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,261,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,374,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[269,374,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), keels on the dorsal scales (absent versus their presence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1046,1156,1658,1684]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Caribicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1046,1156,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Caribicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1164,1269,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1164,1269,1658,1684]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), relative head width (12.0 versus 13.6–17.2), relative frontonasal length (2.46 versus 2.98–3.32), and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 67.1–69.1). From 
<emphasis box="[611,713,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1839" box="[611,708,1730,1756]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Celestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Celestus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[898,993,1730,1756]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[898,993,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1002,1110,1730,1756]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1002,1110,1730,1756]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1839" box="[393,488,1766,1792]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Celestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,488,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Celestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 60.9–66.3). From 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1279,1379,1766,1792]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1279,1379,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[383,478,1802,1828]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[383,478,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[485,590,1802,1828]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[485,590,1802,1828]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1144,1244,1802,1828]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1144,1244,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1251,1356,1802,1828]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1251,1356,1802,1828]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), keels on dorsal scales (absent versus their presence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[688,788,1838,1864]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Comptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[688,788,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Comptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,899,1838,1864]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[794,899,1838,1864]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), relative rostral height (50.1 versus 53.2–65.5), relative frontonasal length (2.46 versus 2.95–3.65), and the relative interparietal distance (0.632 versus 0–0.435). From 
<emphasis box="[220,347,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[220,343,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Panolopus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[528,623,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[528,623,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[631,737,1910,1936]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[631,737,1910,1936]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1307,1427,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1307,1427,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Panolopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 49.7–59.6). From 
<emphasis box="[914,1018,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[914,1014,1946,1972]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sauresia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1194,1289,1946,1972]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1194,1289,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1296,1401,1946,1972]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1296,1401,1946,1972]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the digits per limb (five versus four), the longest toe lamellae (16–17 versus 8–12), the dorsal scale rows (96 versus 101–127), the relative interparietal distance (0.632 versus 0–0.431), and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 63.9–69.9). From 
<emphasis box="[431,564,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName authority="Cochran, 1927" authorityName="Cochran" authorityYear="1927" box="[431,559,187,212]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Wetmorena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Wetmorena</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[738,833,187,213]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[738,833,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[840,944,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[840,944,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
